question: re: your idb post.. i used to be a regular there but left it behind as i saw it get progressively more negative, especially if i ever implied i didn't ship phan. but i did have some interaction with the user who often has a dissenting opinion and was recently told that he should leave by mods. he is by far the NICEST person i had ever interacted with on that website, and even invited me to join a group chat when i said i hadn't made friends in the phandom. i'm sad things got so bad for him there
answer:
That user is pretty badass in my book for continually standing up to the people there, while being constantly berated by the mob. I have never interacted with them, but hearing your story doesn’t surprise since from what I have seen they go out of their way to be respectful of Dan and Phil and to respond very intelligently and politely to people who don’t afford them the same courtesy. They did post a thank you today to people who sent them support privately, but the problem is that so few people speak out against what IDB does publicly. For all the faults the Tumblr and Twitter phandom have, at least people call each other out when lines are crossed. It doesn’t shock me that this person is treated so poorly their because somehow the people who run IDB seem to have cultivated an environment where other people are afraid to or otherwise unwilling to speak out against them, but that one poster draws attention to all the reasons we should.

Could you imagine the reaction here if someone felt entitled to call Dan homophobic and accuse him of using psychological abuse tactics against them for pleading with his so-called fanbase not to cross the lines that THEY are the ones crossing in the first place (make no mistake, there are differences between casual shippers and this crowd)? Yet so many of us stay silent and allow them to attack his character and try to assert control over him by threatening him with further attacks if he goes against their headcannon. Why do people have this idea that Dan was so problematic in 2012 when what he was doing was telling people he felt like he was being “REPEATEDLY VIOLATED” because they were stalking him and his loved ones? It is an idea that they are perpetuating. Why do we allow that? They are still stalking Dan and Phil to this day, finding the address and floorplans to their apartment and secretly passing them around. That’s stalking. The broad legal definition of stalking is, “a crime of engaging in a course of conduct directed at a person that serves no legitimate purpose and seriously alarms, annoys, or intimidates that person.” That is what they and others who subscribe to that ideology have been doing to Dan and Phil for years.

As far as I’m concerned, that person who speaks out against the groupthink that allows them to rationalize and normalize victimizing Dan and Phil for their own entertainment then making a mockery of real social justice issues by using them in defense of behavior that is indefensible, is the truest fan. I hope if I have any voice at all here that anyone reading this will take a moment to think of how they would feel if someone was stalking them and have empathy for the fact that Dan and Phil are real people and how fearful it probably makes them. Why do we allow these people to do this without speaking up? I myself spent a long time not really saying anything too harsh out loud about this group, but it is so wrong and they know it but don’t care, which is the really sad part.

blog.description:
mobile users, click here!

please refer to our FAQ first.

Our goal is to create an alphabetized library of every phanfiction in the phandom. Besides that, we compile masterlists of different genres that are scheduled for posting every few days, and help find fics that have been mislocated.

title: Harry Potter/Hogwarts (8) Masterlist
body:
part one, part two, part three, part four, part five, part six, part seven

Blue Eyes and Paper Doves - pseudophan

Summary:  Dan Howell doesn’t have a lot of friends. None, to be precise. This doesn’t bother him, but it does seem to bother a certain blue eyed Hufflepuff who’s made it his life’s mission to get to know him.

Error 410 - valdimire

Summary: “It cannot deactivate unless you say ‘I am satisfied with my care’.”

Expecto Patronum (ao3) - storming_wolf

Summary: Phil is eager to prove his worth as a powerful wizard, so he attempts to master the Patronus Charm, so Dan helps him find a happier memory.

Howler - queenofallcorgis

Summary: Harry Potter Crossover. Dan is outed in a horrible way and Phil steps in to help.

Hufflepuff and a Slytherin? That will never work! (ao3) - Crazy_panda_25

Summary:
…or will it.

Dan and Phil are starting their first day at Hogwarts school of witchcraft and wizardry. This is a story of there sorting.

Kisses on the Cheek (ao3) - Star4545

Summary: Gryffindor Dan Howell and Hufflepuff Phil Lester meet on the Hogwarts Express. As their time through Hogwarts goes on, Phil starts to kiss people on the cheek, all Dan wants is one simple kiss on his own cheek.

Leaves and Leaving (ao3) - blobfishphil

Summary: In which Phil is a wizard with more than a little bit of a crush on Dan, a muggle.

Little Birdie (fanfiction.net) - Emmazing15

Summary: Dan is the shy son of the Transfiguration professor and Phil is her star student. Dan quietly crushes on him while he is frequently visited by a little blue songbird who likes to sing a very certain tune. (Hogwarts AU)

More Than Just A Hogwarts Hookup (ao3) - morephan

Summary: Dan is a Gryffindor, and Phil is a Hufflepuff. But what happens when PJ comes back to the Hufflepuff dorm with a Gryffindor in Phil’s bed?

Of Timeturners And Nifflers (ao3) - catatonichristy

Summary: Inspired by @laurainlilac’s Hogwarts Professor Au tweets/art.

Spiders and Spells - fiction-phan

Summary: Phil was never great at transfiguration but thought he was getting better. At least he did until Professor McGonagall paired him up to work with Dan Howell. Dan is nice but there’s just one problem. He’s Phil’s crush and Phil is prone to make mistakes when working under pressure.

The Fire that Holds Us Together - succubusphan

Summary: Dan, Phil, Harry and Draco return to Hogwarts for their 8th year and their lives change forever.

The Perfect Prefect (ao3) - Asensical

Summary: A PhandomReverseBang fic inspired by art by Ayushi !

Dan Howell hasn’t spoken to Phil Lester since the boy became a prefect. They used to be best friends, but over the past few years, time has drifted them apart from one another - that is, until an unfortunate game of Quidditch brings them together once again.

The Sleepy Gryffindor (ao3) - sodalester

Summary: Dan has a rough night of sleep. Luckily, Phil’s there for him to nap on.

The Sorting Hat - pasteldanhowells

Summary: Dan’s heading to Hogwarts, but first he meets a boy on the train who becomes his new friend, and he’s nervous about being placed into the Slytherin house. But, maybe things weren’t turn out so bad after all.

The Sorting Hat (wattpad) - pleasepleasenodont

Summary: Dan is a Slytherin with an eye on a certain Hufflepuff, Phil Lester. Do these houses mix?

Whatever Doesn’t Make Me Stronger Kills Me (ao3) - howelnlester (expectopatronuz)

Summary: in Dan’s sixth year, the Triwizard Tournament returns to Hogwarts, as if he needed another damn thing to worry about.
